'''吳弭'''（{{lang-en|Michelle Wu}}；{{bd|1985年|1月14日|||}}），是[[臺灣裔美國人|臺灣裔美國人]]，[[民主党_(美国)|民主黨]]籍政治人物，現任[[波士頓|波士頓]]市長<ref>{{cite web |title=Mayor's Office |url=https://www.boston.gov/departments/mayors-office |website=Boston.gov |accessdate=2021-11-16 |language=en |date=2021-11-16 |archive-date=2022-04-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220406045634/https://www.boston.gov/departments/mayors-office |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

吳弭父母來自台灣，她在[[芝加哥|芝加哥]]長大並畢業于[[哈佛大學|哈佛大學]]，其後受其大學時期的導師、現任麻省[[联邦参议员|参议员]][[伊丽莎白·沃伦|伊丽莎白·沃伦]]影響而開始投身政治。她曾于2016年至2018年間擔任市議會議長，後於[[2021年波士頓市長選舉|2021年波士頓市長選舉]]勝出，成爲該市有史以來首位經選舉產生的女性及非白人市長，及[[波士頓-華盛頓城市帶|美國東岸]]首位亞裔市長<ref>{{cite web |title=Number of Asian Americans leading major cities could grow by 3. That's big, advocates say. |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/elections/number-asian-americans-leading-major-cities-could-grow-3-s-n1269577 |website=NBC News |accessdate=2021-09-15 |language=en |date=2021-06-09 |archive-date=2021-11-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211121175444/https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/elections/number-asian-americans-leading-major-cities-could-grow-3-s-n1269577 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

==早年==
吳弭出生于美国伊利诺州芝加哥市[[南区_(芝加哥)|南區]]，她的名字是由爺爺取的，「弭」一字表示消停的意思，也意味著和平，而家裡四個姊妹兄弟的名字都是弓字旁<ref>{{cite news |title=人物側寫／吳弭打破族群藩籬 就任現實仍待「弭」 |url=https://www.worldjournal.com/wj/story/121186/6236814 |accessdate=2022-04-15 |work=世界新聞網 |date=2022-04-13 |language=zh-TW |archive-date=2022-05-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220526063529/https://www.worldjournal.com/wj/story/121186/6236814 }}</ref>。她的祖父祖母老家在北京，外婆是四川人，外公是廣東人，是一位[[中華民國國軍|國軍]]將軍，他們在1949年[[國共内戰|國共内戰]]后離開[[中國大陸|中國大陸]]移居[[台灣|台灣]]<ref>{{cite web|title=【人物專訪】吳弭—中華文化孕育出的優秀女兒|url=https://www.epochtimes.com/b5/13/7/27/n3926869.htm|publisher=大紀元|accessdate=2021-11-03|archive-date=2021-11-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211103181107/https://www.epochtimes.com/b5/13/7/27/n3926869.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。吳弭的雙親在台北出生長大，在1980年代移民到[[美國|美國]]<ref name="Women Top Boston At-Large City Councilor Race">{{cite web|title=Women Top Boston At-Large City Councilor Race|url=http://www.wbur.org/2013/11/06/women-top-boston-at-large-city-councilor-race|publisher=WBUR|accessdate=24 January 2014|archive-date=2016-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304052555/http://www.wbur.org/2013/11/06/women-top-boston-at-large-city-councilor-race|dead-url=no}}</ref>，不久后父母離異<ref name=jonas/><ref name="liuCrimson">{{cite web |last1=Liu |first1=Samuel E. |title=Boston City Councilor Wu '07 Fights for Causes Close to Home {{!}} News {{!}} The Harvard Crimson |url=https://www.thecrimson.com/article/2015/4/7/michelle-wu-council-feature/ |website=www.thecrimson.com |publisher=The Harvard Crimson |access-date=10 January 2021 |date=9 November 2017 |archive-date=2021-08-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210815170152/https://www.thecrimson.com/article/2015/4/7/michelle-wu-council-feature/ |dead-url=no }}</ref> 。2003年，她從{{Link-en|巴靈頓高中|Barrington High School}}畢業，並獲得了{{Link-en|美國總統獎學金|Presidential_Scholars_Program}}到哈佛大學修讀<ref>{{cite web |title=After Two Years as Boston City Council President, Michelle Wu Steps Down to Focus on Policy |url=https://bunewsservice.com/michelle-wu-steps-down-to-focus-on-policy/ |website=Boston University News Service |language=en |date=24 January 2018 |access-date=2021-07-07 |archive-date=2021-07-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210711193703/https://bunewsservice.com/michelle-wu-steps-down-to-focus-on-policy/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="2003 Presidential Scholars Program">{{cite web|title=2003 Presidential Scholars Program|url=http://www2.ed.gov/programs/psp/2003/yearbook.pdf|publisher=U.S. Department of Education|accessdate=24 January 2014|archive-date=2021-07-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210713161657/https://www2.ed.gov/programs/psp/2003/yearbook.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>，其後她在2007年取得學士學位，再于2012年獲得同校法學院的[[法律博士|法律博士]]學位<ref name="Michelle Wu shows promise for city’s future">{{cite web|title=Michelle Wu shows promise for city's future|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/metro/2013/04/02/meet-michelle-city-council-candidate-who-wants-help-shape-boston-future/Gzym6U189B3Cm1TMRxMTEN/story.html|publisher=Boston Globe|accessdate=24 January 2014|archive-date=2021-07-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210712001141/https://www.bostonglobe.com/metro/2013/04/02/meet-michelle-city-council-candidate-who-wants-help-shape-boston-future/Gzym6U189B3Cm1TMRxMTEN/story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。她的母語為[[中華民國國語|華語]]，同時能說[[西班牙語|西班牙語]]<ref name=jonas/>。

==生涯與經歷==
從哈佛大學畢業后，吳弭加入[[波士頓諮詢公司|波士頓諮詢公司]]並成爲諮詢顧問<ref>{{cite web |last1=WEISS-MEYER |first1=AMY L. |title=Case Study: Consulting After College |url=https://www.thecrimson.com/article/2014/11/6/consulting-after-harvard-fm/ |website=The Crimson |accessdate=2 November 2020 |archive-date=2021-05-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210506102401/https://www.thecrimson.com/article/2014/11/6/consulting-after-harvard-fm/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。但其後因爲其母得病，她不得已辭去工作並搬回芝加哥去照顧其母與年幼的兄弟姐妹<ref name="liuCrimson"/> 。同時，爲了幫補家計她在當地開了[[茶館|茶館]]<ref name="liuCrimson"/> 。2009年，她回到哈佛法學院修讀法學博士學位<ref name="liuCrimson"/>。

2010年，吳弭開始在[[波士顿市政厅|波士顿市政厅]]的財務及管理局工作，時任市長為[[汤玛斯·曼尼诺|汤玛斯·曼尼诺]]。其後她在曼尼诺的幕僚長Mitch Weiss安排下轉到{{Link-en|Rappaport法律服務中心|Rappaport Center for Law and Public Service}}工作<ref name="Rappaport Briefing, July 2011">{{cite web|url=http://www.suffolk.edu/documents/LawRappaportCenter/RappaportBriefingFall2011.pdf|title=Rappaport Briefing, July 2011|publisher=The Rappaport Center for Law and Public Service|accessdate=24 January 2014|archive-date=2016-08-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160821064610/http://www.suffolk.edu/documents/LawRappaportCenter/RappaportBriefingFall2011.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在此期間，她利用以前開茶館的經驗，為波士頓的餐飲業界制定了首部開業指南<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cityofboston.gov/Images_Documents/restaurant%20guide_final_tcm3-19418.pdf |title=Restaurant Roadmap |publisher=City of Boston |accessdate=24 January 2014 |url-status=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131020095154/http://www.cityofboston.gov/Images_Documents/restaurant%20guide_final_tcm3-19418.pdf |archivedate=2013-10-20 }}</ref>，以協助當地餐飲業界發展。同時她亦積極在波士頓社區推進[[美食车|餐飲車]]計劃，最後成功在市政厅廣場導入了數台餐飲車，為波士頓首例<ref>{{cite web|url=http://edibleboston.com/the-boston-challenge/|title=THE BOSTON FOOD TRUCK CHALLENGE|publisher=edibleBOSTON|accessdate=24 January 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140202182630/http://edibleboston.com/the-boston-challenge/|archive-date=2014-02-02|url-status=yes}}</ref> 。2011年，她開始在{{Link-en|波士頓醫療中心|Boston_Medical_Center}}為低收入的患者們提供法律咨詢服務<ref name="Rappaport Briefing, July 2011"/>。

2012年，吳弭在哈佛法學院時的導師－伊丽莎白·沃伦宣佈競選联邦参议员，而她也成爲沃伦的競選團成員。在沃伦競選期間，吳弭與不同的選民組織接觸，包括[[有色人種|有色人種]]，[[LGBTQ|LGBTQ]]團體，[[退伍軍人|退伍軍人]]，[[女性主义|女性主义]]團體等等<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bostonmagazine.com/news/blog/2013/08/09/candidate-chat-michelle-wu/|title=City Council Candidate Chat: Michelle Wu|publisher=The Dorchester Reporter|accessdate=24 January 2014|archive-date=2016-05-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160531182750/http://www.bostonmagazine.com/news/blog/2013/08/09/candidate-chat-michelle-wu/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。其後沃伦成功擊敗挑战争取连任的共和党代表[[史考特·布朗|史考特·布朗]]，成爲了麻萨诸塞州的首位女性联邦参议员。

===波士頓市議會（2014年-2021年）===
[[File:Michelle_Wu_at_2013_Allston_Brighton_Parade_(51363685549)_(1).png|thumb]]
2013年，吳弭首次參與了波士頓市議會的選舉，并在同年11月首次當選為議員，而其後3次的選舉她都取得了勝利。在議員任内，吳弭主要關注改革波士頓的發牌與審批制度<ref name=Irons>{{cite news|last=Meghan E.|first=Irons|title=New look urged for Boston's silly old rules|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/metro/2014/02/26/councilor-michelle-pushes-ease-permitting-and-licensing-process/f4PHNqlDOiMY18UYTyTXUK/story.html|accessdate=26 February 2014|newspaper=[[The_Boston_Globe|The Boston Globe]]|date=26 February 2014|archive-date=2021-07-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210711115634/https://www.bostonglobe.com/metro/2014/02/26/councilor-michelle-pushes-ease-permitting-and-licensing-process/f4PHNqlDOiMY18UYTyTXUK/story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。她參與通過了批准市政員工取得有薪產假的法例。

[[File:It's_Boston_City_Councilor_At-Large_Michelle_Wu_@wutrain_at_the_-DorchesterDay_Parade_(18733700962).jpg|thumb]]
